article.headline: Alabama State 71, Grambling 66
article.story: MONTGOMERY, Ala. (AP) -- Ralfeal Golden hit a 3-pointer in overtime and finished with 26 points and eight rebounds, leading Alabama State to a 71-66 victory over Grambling State on Wednesday night. Grambling State tied the game 59-all on a pair of free throws by Marcus Watson with 6 seconds left. Golden missed a 3-pointer, forcing the teams into overtime. Golden's 3 with 56 seconds remaining in overtime put Alabama State in front 66-65, and the Hornets wouldn't trail again. Golden shot nine of 18 from the field and five of seven from the foul line for Alabama State (4-7, 2-0 SWAC). Alexander Oliver added 11 points and LaMarquis Blake had 10. Ron Ellis and Watson scored 14 points apiece to lead Grambling State (4-5, 1-1), while Brion Rush and Andre Ratliff each added 10. John Dorsey pulled down a game-high 10 rebounds for the Tigers. Grambling State led 29-25 at halftime, but was held to 25 percent shooting in the second half. The Hornets dominated the boards 39-33
